caption.p: Effects of the extracts on high glucose-induced ROS accumulation in SH-SY5Y cells. Relative intracellular ROS level of SH-SY5Y cells treated with 100 mM glucose alone or combined with different concentrations for either CHP ( a) or CHL ( b) for 24 h. The effect of DMSO on relative intracellular ROS level of SH-SY5Y cells treated with (0.001 to 0.025% ( v/ v)) DMSO alone ( c). Data are presented as the means ± SD, * p < 0.05 vs. control; ** p < 0.05 vs. 100 mM glucose alone. For CHP, p value was 0.002 in both 100 mM glucose and 1 µg/mL groups. For CHL, p value was 0.000 in both 100 mM glucose and 1 µg/mL groups.
